      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOOTSIE (2) is racing well without winning, recording four minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when third (20.25) over 350m at this track. Rates highly and will give a great sight. NEWBROCK TILLY (7) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (24.84) at Sale over 435m. Expected to be in the finish again. WHY NOT AVA (4) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow sixth (17.11) over 300m at Healesville. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Has ability and can atone. CATCH A CUTIE (3) generally performs well from this box.",
